title: San Juan Island National Historical Park: Photo Gallery
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Photos & Multimedia     Photo Gallery               Photo Gallery                    Prescribed Fire on Young Hill 6-23-14   14 Photos  Fire crews from the National Park Service, U.S. Forest Service and San Juan County completed a successful prescribed fire on a 15-acre section of Young Hill's south slope at English Camp. The fire commenced at 11 a.m. and was completed by 2:45 p.m.          Mitchell Trail Work   5 Photos  Through a cooperative effort between the park and citizen representing mixed recreational users, the Mitchell Hill trail network promises to become one of the top recreational venues on the island.          Bald Eagles of American Camp   10 Photos  The American Camp bald eagles' nest has been a constant in the visitor parking area for more than 12 years.            English Camp Historical Images   15 Photos            English Camp: A Family Album   13 Photos            Prairie Life   14 Photos  Images of of one of the last natural prairie in the Puget Sound/Northern Straits region of Washington State.            Wildflowers   22 Photos  Wildflowers          Annual Encampments   11 Photos  Each July re-enactors from throughout the Pacific Northwest and Canada gather for the annuel Encampment that commeorates the peaceful joint occupation of San Juan Island from 1860 to 1872.
